# Description: Detects suspicious DNS queries that may use DGA.
# --------------------------------------------
#designed to detect suspicious DNS queries that may be generated by Domain Generation Algorithms (DGAs) â€” a technique commonly used by malware to contact command-and-control (C2) servers.
# example : ab3jd9fjsk2mf8wlsnd0.com
index=dns sourcetype=dns_logs
| regex query="^[a-zA-Z0-9]{20,}\.com$"
| stats count by query, client_ip
